        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Louis, Missouri,</placeName>
                <date>December 5, 1858.</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser,</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Honored Sir: Herewith I transmit<lb/> to you the action of both
                congregations of this<lb/> city with regard to the <persName>Mortara</persName>*
                affair.<lb/> At the same time I hope that <persName>Mr. Lattin</persName> or
                someone<lb/> else has already sent you this report, since at the<lb/> moment, I am
                ill. Ever since the time<lb/> when I unfortunately lost both my sisters on the<lb/>
                steamer “Austria, I have been ill and quite<lb/> upset. I must also call your
                attention to one<lb/> thing, that the Catholic church committed<lb/> a dastardly
                act. A certain Jew was deathly<lb/> sick and was <sic>baptised</sic> against his
                will.<lb/> Through the influence of <persName>Mrs. Lattin</persName> and
                    <persName>Friede</persName><lb/> he was buried in a Jewish grave. The
                presidents<lb/> of both congregations were very active in this<lb/> matter and
                deserve praise. Also in the<lb/> matter of the <persName>Mortara</persName> affair,
                Messrs. <persName>Lattin</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Friede</persName> and <persName>Bush</persName> were very active.
                    <del>Also</del> $165 was also sent through me for <del>the</del> aid to
                    <placeName>New<lb/> Orleans</placeName> and the B'nai Brith sent $150—
                together<lb/> $265 from here, which is a sufficiently large<lb/> sum from
                    <placeName>St. Louis</placeName>. The Polish synagogue will be<lb/> ready for
                Passover and then I hope that the Jews, that<lb/> is the Poles and the Englishmen,
                will more diligently<lb/> attend service, which has not been the case until
                now.<lb/> Farewell, such is the wish of<lb/> Your friend,<lb/>
                <persName role="author">H. Kuttner</persName><lb/>
            </p>
            <p>*The famous case of the baptism and kidnapping by<lb/> the Catholic church of a
                Jewish child. See Jewish Encyclopedia<lb/>
            </p>
        </body>
